         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Some simplification among the genera of Coniferae is necessary. You  ¶  ¶ will have observed that I insisted on the reduction of Frenela to Callitris in my elucidation of the fossil genus Spondylos...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.05.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 37.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The correspondent is identified as Bentham since M knew he would be working during 1872 on the <name key="Coniferae">Coniferae</name> for Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6; see J. Hooker to M, 20 November 1872.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS dated to May 1871 as the earliest possible date it could have been sent, given M's reference to his published description of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Spondylostrobus">Spondylostrobus</name>
                     </seg> in B71.05.02. The reference to B71.06.02, listed as a 'recent publication' by the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg> on 6 June 1871, p. 6, suggests that M expected his note to reach Bentham before this publication did.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Some simplification among the genera of <name key="Coniferae">Coniferae</name> is necessary. You <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will have observed that I insisted on the reduction of <name key="Frenela">Frenela</name> to <name key="Callitris">Callitris</name> in my elucidation of the fossil genus <name key="Spondylostrobus">Spondylostrobus</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B71.05.02, p.49, where M also treated <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Actinostrobus</seg> as a sub-genus of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Callitris">Callitris</name>
                     </seg>; see also B71.06.02, p. 33. Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6, p. 239, preferred <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Frenela">Frenela</name>
                     </seg> to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Callitris">Callitris</name>
                     </seg>. </p>
               </note> You will find the<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>in </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">omitted between</seg>
                     <seg style=""> find </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">and</seg>
                     <seg style=""> the?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> appendix to the Accl. Soc. Report for this year also <name key="Retinospora">Retinospora</name> [reduced] as well as <name key="Chamaecyparis">Chamaecyparis</name> to <name key="Cupressus">Cupressus</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B71.06.02; both generic reductions are on p. 31.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
